WEBVTT

00:00.863 --> 00:03.937
We're gonna have some fun tonight, Pawnee!
[All cheering]

00:04.122 --> 00:06.606
Who is ready to play 60?

00:06.657 --> 00:07.924
Everybody on the field!

00:07.959 --> 00:10.127
Yeah!

00:10.161 --> 00:13.174
The NFL has a campaign
to try to get kids active

00:13.294 --> 00:14.511
for 60 minutes per day.

00:14.562 --> 00:15.946
And so we bused in

00:15.980 --> 00:17.931
a hundred lucky,
little buggers from Pawnee.

00:17.965 --> 00:20.517
And they are gonna get a chance
to play with the Colts.

00:20.551 --> 00:22.302
Oh! Come on, Reggie!

00:22.336 --> 00:23.616
I told you to run a button hook.

00:23.637 --> 00:24.821
- I did, Leslie.
- Okay.

00:24.856 --> 00:25.956
I guess you would know.

00:25.990 --> 00:27.874
A pleasure to see you again,
Mr. Luck.

00:27.908 --> 00:29.125
We met briefly last year

00:29.177 --> 00:31.678
- at our friend's bachelor party.
- Oh, yeah. Right.

00:31.712 --> 00:32.863
How are you?

00:32.897 --> 00:34.080
I normally don't answer
that question,

00:34.115 --> 00:35.699
but since I respect
your talent,

00:35.750 --> 00:38.117
I will tell you--
I am fine.

00:38.135 --> 00:39.102
Hi, I'm April.

00:39.136 --> 00:43.356
I stole your wallet.

00:43.390 --> 00:44.724
You guys are weird.

00:44.742 --> 00:46.960
Thank you.

00:46.994 --> 00:47.961
What's up, girl?

00:47.995 --> 00:50.296
Keep walking, 98.

00:50.314 --> 00:52.115
You don't even want to talk
to that guy?

00:52.149 --> 00:54.601
- He plays for the NFL.
- He's a linebacker.

00:54.619 --> 00:58.221
Skill positions only
for Donna Meagle.

00:58.256 --> 00:59.505
I got my Colts beanie,

00:59.523 --> 01:00.473
my Colts scarf,

01:00.507 --> 01:01.892
I got the Colts grill going,

01:01.943 --> 01:04.411
and the crowning glory--
Colts slippies.

01:04.444 --> 01:06.162
How are you going
to run in those?

01:06.214 --> 01:08.915
[Laughing]
"Run"? Tommy doesn't run.

01:08.949 --> 01:10.217
That's your guys' job.

01:10.251 --> 01:13.320
Now, uh, let's go fetch
this football throw, fellas.

01:15.406 --> 01:16.957
I love sports.

01:16.991 --> 01:19.926
[Triumphant music]

01:19.961 --> 01:30.839
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny</font>
<font color="#ec14bd">www.addic7ed.com</font>

01:37.464 --> 01:39.763
Check it out, Tom--
the Eagleton reservoir.

01:39.797 --> 01:40.830
Isn't it stunning?

01:40.865 --> 01:42.082
It's just a big dumb pond.

01:42.116 --> 01:43.700
This morning I saw
a YouTube clip

01:43.751 --> 01:45.335
of a little puppy riding
a motorcycle.

01:45.369 --> 01:47.103
So my bar for "stunning"
is pretty high.

01:47.138 --> 01:49.889
What if I told you that
this water has fluoride in it?

01:49.923 --> 01:51.908
Then I would tell you
the puppy had a little side car

01:51.943 --> 01:53.693
with a piggy in it
named Hampton.

01:53.727 --> 01:55.912
First of all,
send me a link to that video.

01:55.963 --> 01:58.131
But more importantly,
now that we have access

01:58.149 --> 02:00.767
to the Eagleton reservoir
and the water-treatment supply,

02:00.801 --> 02:02.769
Pawnee is going to have fluoride
in its water

02:02.787 --> 02:04.554
for the first time
in our history,

02:04.588 --> 02:06.139
our oral history.

02:06.173 --> 02:07.440
Nailed it.

02:07.475 --> 02:09.514
Of course I'm upset
that I lost the recall election.

02:09.526 --> 02:12.078
But I'm just gonna spend
the remainder of my term

02:12.112 --> 02:14.848
cramming in as many
good projects as I can.

02:14.882 --> 02:17.183
Lame duck?
Try flame duck...

02:17.217 --> 02:20.086
'cause this duck is on fire.

02:20.121 --> 02:21.538
It's hard doing
stupid government stuff

02:21.589 --> 02:23.006
now that Rent-a-Swag's closed.

02:23.040 --> 02:24.874
I'm a businessman.
That's what I was born to do.

02:24.909 --> 02:27.093
Well, look, you just got
to make the most of the job

02:27.111 --> 02:28.561
that you have.

02:28.595 --> 02:30.263
Like, take that trash collector.

02:30.281 --> 02:31.998
It's not the most glamorous job
in the world,

02:32.033 --> 02:33.917
but he's doing it
with a smile on his face.

02:33.951 --> 02:35.669
Oh, my God.

02:35.703 --> 02:37.971
He's not wearing any pants.
What's wrong with him?

02:38.005 --> 02:39.806
- Let's get out of here.
- He's smiling at us!

02:39.824 --> 02:41.908
- Let's go! Run!
- [Whimpering]

02:41.942 --> 02:43.910
What's so exciting, everyone?

02:43.928 --> 02:45.762
Look what Ron made.
It's amazing.

02:45.813 --> 02:47.847
Several months ago,
I was on a walk

02:47.865 --> 02:49.666
and found my crib tree.

02:49.700 --> 02:52.152
I approached the tree,
murdered it,

02:52.186 --> 02:54.087
left it to cure in my woodshop,

02:54.105 --> 02:55.722
and have begun working it
into a crib

02:55.740 --> 02:57.407
for my upcoming child.

02:57.441 --> 03:00.243
Ron Swanson,
you cannot use this crib.

03:00.294 --> 03:02.545
You're ignoring every known
crib-safety standard.

03:02.596 --> 03:04.264
It's all covered in
the parenting book I'm reading.

03:04.298 --> 03:06.333
Are you going to crawl my way?
By Lenny Kravitz.

03:06.367 --> 03:08.668
My crib will be safe
because I'm building it

03:08.703 --> 03:10.120
with my own two hands.

03:10.171 --> 03:11.588
I bought my crib
in Bloomington,

03:11.639 --> 03:14.190
and I am confident
that it is literally

03:14.241 --> 03:16.443
the safest crib
in the explored universe.

03:16.477 --> 03:17.444
Let me take you there,

03:17.478 --> 03:18.928
and you can talk
to the salesperson.

03:18.963 --> 03:20.096
Counteroffer--

03:20.131 --> 03:22.265
you take me nowhere,
and I talk to no one.

03:22.299 --> 03:23.350
Counter-counteroffer--

03:23.384 --> 03:24.984
you come with me,
or I make you attend

03:25.019 --> 03:26.986
a four-hour fax cover-sheet
protocol meeting.

03:27.004 --> 03:29.806
Either way, it's a win for me.

03:29.840 --> 03:32.776
Next on the docket is
a vote to approve

03:32.810 --> 03:34.861
the Pawnee-Eagleton
reservoir merger.

03:34.895 --> 03:36.246
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

03:36.280 --> 03:39.332
We're just goosing our
water supply with fluoride?

03:39.366 --> 03:40.666
I mean, come on.

03:40.684 --> 03:42.652
Are we really gonna force
every Pawnee resident

03:42.686 --> 03:45.438
to ingest a chemical
we know nothing about?

03:45.473 --> 03:47.573
Fluoride is used
by the communists

03:47.591 --> 03:49.075
to control our minds.

03:49.093 --> 03:50.543
No, it's not.

03:50.561 --> 03:51.861
Fluoride can control minds?

03:51.896 --> 03:54.831
Like, you can use it
to make ladies do stuff?

03:54.865 --> 03:56.545
How am I the one
that is getting booted off

03:56.550 --> 03:57.467
of this city council?

03:57.501 --> 03:59.419
Okay, fluoride is safe,

03:59.437 --> 04:00.720
it is good for you,

04:00.738 --> 04:03.940
and almost every town
in America uses it.

04:03.991 --> 04:05.141
Ah, all right.

04:05.176 --> 04:06.376
You got me.

04:06.427 --> 04:07.877
I don't want fluoride
in the water

04:07.928 --> 04:10.480
because I'm a dentist,
and I like cavities.

04:10.514 --> 04:11.948
Yeah, that is not
a valid reason.

04:11.982 --> 04:13.232
Pawnee's cavity problem

04:13.250 --> 04:15.051
is why a small-town dentist,

04:15.086 --> 04:19.139
like me, can afford
such a boss ride.

04:19.173 --> 04:21.491
Got an Asian girl
to sit in it once.

04:21.524 --> 04:23.760
Why did we come out here?

04:23.794 --> 04:25.244
Come on, Jamm.

04:25.262 --> 04:27.313
Fluoride in the water--
it's a no-brainer.

04:27.348 --> 04:28.681
Can't you just let me
have this one?

04:28.699 --> 04:30.016
No can do, Knopey.

04:30.034 --> 04:32.118
As a matter of fact,
I would like to propose

04:32.152 --> 04:34.838
my own bill--
the Pawnee Clean Water Bill,

04:34.889 --> 04:37.307
which prohibits adding anything

04:37.358 --> 04:40.092
to our water supply forever.

04:40.111 --> 04:41.895
Jamm's not going to be able

04:41.929 --> 04:44.297
to kill this reservoir merger,
is he?

04:44.331 --> 04:46.866
On my side, I have facts,
science, and reason.

04:46.901 --> 04:48.334
All he has
is fear-mongering.

04:48.352 --> 04:50.236
Oh, my God, he's gonna win.

04:50.271 --> 04:52.638
Yeah, people get jittery
about stuff like this.

04:52.656 --> 04:54.791
Remember last year
when no one would get flu shots

04:54.825 --> 04:57.210
'cause there was a rumor
they turned you European?

04:57.244 --> 04:58.711
Well,
I'll figure something out.

04:58.729 --> 05:00.146
Oh, Jessica's here.
I better go.

05:00.181 --> 05:02.015
- Okay, bye.
- Hey, sugar butt.

05:02.049 --> 05:05.652
Some lardos in Muncie ate
tainted Sweetums toffee sticks

05:05.686 --> 05:08.471
and diarrhea'd so much,
they ended up in the hospital.

05:08.506 --> 05:09.472
Ugh.

05:09.507 --> 05:10.640
Can we give their school,

05:10.691 --> 05:12.592
like, a new seesaw
or something?

05:12.610 --> 05:13.593
Yeah.

05:13.611 --> 05:15.728
Thanks.

05:15.746 --> 05:18.164
The new site looks good.
Nice work.

05:18.198 --> 05:20.233
Oh, my God.
These dogs are so cute.

05:20.267 --> 05:22.168
I want to throw up
and kill myself.

05:22.186 --> 05:25.438
Animal control had to take in
all the pets from Eagleton.

05:25.472 --> 05:27.657
And Crazy Craig used to run
all their shelters,

05:27.708 --> 05:29.542
so he helped me make
an adoption website

05:29.576 --> 05:30.576
for all the dogs.

05:30.594 --> 05:31.878
If you can look at that site

05:31.896 --> 05:33.217
and not want to take home
50 dogs,

05:33.230 --> 05:35.932
you're basically
a war criminal.

05:35.983 --> 05:37.033
[Groans]

05:37.067 --> 05:38.034
See the way that dog

05:38.085 --> 05:39.318
is rolling around in a puddle?

05:39.336 --> 05:41.588
That's something Andy does
when he gets hot.

05:41.622 --> 05:42.955
Oh, my God, you're right.

05:42.973 --> 05:44.023
That is so Andy.

05:44.058 --> 05:45.424
Oh, my God.
That dog is totally...

05:45.442 --> 05:46.776
Both: Tom!

05:46.810 --> 05:48.027
I don't know why.
It doesn't look like him.

05:48.061 --> 05:49.462
But it just is.

05:49.497 --> 05:50.863
It's like the dog is
the essence of Tom.

05:50.881 --> 05:52.382
[Gasps]
Okay, important meeting

05:52.433 --> 05:53.800
in the conference room
right now.

05:53.834 --> 05:56.335
We are going to all pick
our spirit dogs.

05:56.353 --> 05:57.987
Oh, I've got to pick up Gayle
at the airport.

05:58.022 --> 05:59.605
Larry, I swear to God,

05:59.623 --> 06:01.274
if you leave right now,
we will make your spirit dog

06:01.292 --> 06:02.825
a miniature schnauzer.

06:02.877 --> 06:04.427
- Is that bad?
- Yes!

06:04.461 --> 06:06.062
Get in there!

06:06.096 --> 06:08.231
Ann found this place.

06:08.265 --> 06:10.033
It's where we bought
our "Sounds of Nature" machine.

06:10.067 --> 06:12.652
You bought a machine
that replicates

06:12.686 --> 06:14.320
an open window?

06:14.354 --> 06:15.321
Frasier!
Chris Traeger.

06:15.339 --> 06:16.506
Do you remember me?

06:16.540 --> 06:17.957
I came in here looking
for the Vanna White book

06:17.991 --> 06:19.325
on child care--

06:19.343 --> 06:21.961
<i>I'd like to solve the puzzle</i>
<i>of parenting.</i>

06:21.995 --> 06:23.029
Could you show my friend, Ron,

06:23.063 --> 06:24.631
that amazing crib
that you sold me?

06:24.665 --> 06:27.066
The Babylove L'il Sweetheart
Safe 4 Ever and Ever model.

06:27.100 --> 06:28.751
Oh, yeah,
that thing is a deathtrap.

06:28.786 --> 06:30.403
- I'm sorry?
- Just found out this morning--

06:30.421 --> 06:31.538
it's being recalled.

06:31.572 --> 06:33.406
They found maxicylofentabol
in the glue.

06:33.424 --> 06:34.641
Is that good?
It sounds bad.

06:34.675 --> 06:36.726
It burned off my fingernails.

06:36.760 --> 06:40.029
I'll be in the car.

06:40.064 --> 06:43.666
Councilwoman Leslie Knope
wants to put fluoride,

06:43.701 --> 06:46.119
which is a chemical,
into your drinking water.

06:46.153 --> 06:47.720
You know what else is
a chemical?

06:47.755 --> 06:50.006
Strychnine and cyanide.

06:50.057 --> 06:51.123
- What?
- And dirt...

06:51.141 --> 06:53.626
and rust and even broken glass.

06:53.644 --> 06:55.194
Exactly.

06:55.229 --> 06:56.779
You definitely understand
what chemicals are, Perd.

06:56.814 --> 06:59.966
I would suggest if you want
to contact the psychopath

07:00.000 --> 07:02.785
that wants to turn your kids
into bad-at-math,

07:02.820 --> 07:04.954
communist fluoride zombies,

07:04.989 --> 07:06.856
well, just call the number
at the bottom of your screen.

07:06.890 --> 07:08.658
[Phone rings]

07:08.709 --> 07:09.959
Leslie Knope.

07:09.994 --> 07:11.878
Stop right there.
You know what?

07:11.912 --> 07:12.962
Fluoride protects your teeth,

07:12.997 --> 07:14.831
and it's perfectly healthy
for you.

07:14.882 --> 07:17.283
Well, if Jamm says that,
then he is a lying idiot,

07:17.301 --> 07:19.836
and if you believe it,
then so are you.

07:19.887 --> 07:21.137
[Phone receiver thuds]
Whoa.

07:21.171 --> 07:22.972
You just talked to that person
like I talk to you.

07:23.007 --> 07:24.140
- You can't do that.
- Why not?

07:24.174 --> 07:27.510
What are they gonna do,
kick me out of office?

07:27.561 --> 07:29.095
Why did it take me so long
to realize this?

07:29.129 --> 07:31.464
There are no consequences
to my actions anymore.

07:31.482 --> 07:34.467
No matter what I do, literally
nothing bad can happen to me.

07:34.485 --> 07:36.436
I'm like
a white, male U.S. senator.

07:36.470 --> 07:38.104
[Phone rings]

07:38.138 --> 07:41.407
Fluoride is going
into the water, moron.

07:41.442 --> 07:44.477
Oh. Hey, mom.
Sorry.

07:44.495 --> 07:46.913
Because all it does
is prevent cavities!

07:46.947 --> 07:48.448
God!

07:48.482 --> 07:50.583
I expected more from you.

07:53.197 --> 07:55.161
Right.
I'm a loose cannon.

07:55.281 --> 07:56.898
We need to fight
fire with fire.

07:56.916 --> 07:59.001
I call a town hall meeting,
I gather everyone together,

07:59.035 --> 08:00.469
I distribute the binders,

08:00.503 --> 08:03.989
but now the binders are
bright yellow!

08:04.023 --> 08:05.657
Om!

08:05.692 --> 08:07.576
[Imitates explosion]

08:07.610 --> 08:10.062
- Too extreme?
- Too nothing.

08:10.096 --> 08:11.897
Look, Jamm's
already ruined fluoride.

08:11.948 --> 08:13.115
Everyone's scared of it.

08:13.149 --> 08:14.433
What if we just called it
something else?

08:14.467 --> 08:15.584
What do you mean?

08:15.618 --> 08:16.751
I mean we rebrand.

08:16.769 --> 08:18.353
No one cared
about Calvin Broadus

08:18.388 --> 08:21.189
until he started calling
himself Snoop Doggy Dogg.

08:21.207 --> 08:22.624
Then when people got tired
of that,

08:22.658 --> 08:23.658
he went by Snoop Dogg,

08:23.676 --> 08:25.310
and now he's Snoop Lion.

08:25.345 --> 08:27.546
What's he gonna be
in ten years--Snoop Laser Snake?

08:27.580 --> 08:28.830
Who knows?

08:28.865 --> 08:30.732
What are you saying--
we need to sex up fluoride?

08:30.750 --> 08:31.833
I don't know, Tom.

08:31.868 --> 08:33.467
It's a pretty sexy topic
already.

08:33.503 --> 08:36.054
Leslie, you got to give people
something to get excited about.

08:36.105 --> 08:37.356
You told me to make
the most of my job.

08:37.407 --> 08:38.624
I'm good at this stuff.

08:38.658 --> 08:40.942
Now, are you
a loose cannon or not?

08:40.960 --> 08:42.510
Yeah.

08:42.544 --> 08:44.429
I'm as loose as a goose.

08:44.464 --> 08:45.897
Do your thing, Tom.

08:45.949 --> 08:47.566
Aw.

08:47.617 --> 08:49.701
Now, remember,
it's about finding a dog

08:49.752 --> 08:50.886
that captures your spirit.

08:50.920 --> 08:53.722
- See? This is Craig.
- [Chuckles]

08:53.756 --> 08:55.440
Oh, no!
That is insane!

08:55.491 --> 08:57.526
I will burn this place
to the ground

08:57.560 --> 08:59.027
if you pick that one!

08:59.045 --> 09:00.462
Okay, good choice.

09:00.496 --> 09:02.297
You guys, Leslie.

09:02.315 --> 09:03.649
Yes!
And...

09:03.700 --> 09:05.100
Ron Swanson.

09:05.118 --> 09:06.568
- Oh!
- Oh, my God.

09:06.586 --> 09:08.670
- This is Larry.
- That's great.

09:08.704 --> 09:10.672
Bingo. Donna.
Nailed it.

09:10.690 --> 09:12.190
- Ooh.
- [Laughs]

09:12.241 --> 09:15.544
Because you're pretty
and you like makeup and stuff.

09:15.578 --> 09:17.329
Game over.

09:20.566 --> 09:23.986
Ron, I want to do things
the Swanson way.

09:24.020 --> 09:25.337
Wonderful.

09:25.388 --> 09:27.255
First rule--
no conversation lasts longer

09:27.273 --> 09:29.024
than 100 total words.

09:29.058 --> 09:31.393
You have used 9.
I have used 20.

09:31.427 --> 09:32.861
- Continue.
- Fun.

09:32.879 --> 09:35.030
I'd like you to teach me
to build a crib.

09:35.048 --> 09:37.349
Why do you need to build
your own crib?

09:37.400 --> 09:38.734
Because I no longer trust
anything

09:38.768 --> 09:40.369
other than my own two hands.

09:40.403 --> 09:42.437
It is debilitating,
but exciting.

09:42.472 --> 09:44.740
Okay, we'll go to my woodshop
at lunch.

09:44.774 --> 09:46.224
Wonderful.
Look at us--

09:46.275 --> 09:48.193
both standing
on the cusp of fatherhood.

09:48.227 --> 09:49.995
I know we haven't spent
a lot of time together,

09:50.029 --> 09:51.747
- but--
- 100.

09:54.192 --> 09:56.051
All right, so, in conclusion...

09:56.069 --> 09:57.219
fluoride, chemical,

09:57.253 --> 09:59.638
tiny genitals, misinformation,

09:59.672 --> 10:03.642
panic, death, Jenny McCarthy.

10:03.676 --> 10:06.528
Well, I don't know, councilman.

10:06.562 --> 10:07.863
That was a little dry.

10:07.897 --> 10:09.864
What do you say
we have some fun, huh?

10:09.882 --> 10:11.767
Check this.

10:11.801 --> 10:13.719
Plain water?
Yuck.

10:13.770 --> 10:15.437
I'm bored.

10:15.455 --> 10:16.604
Then try this.

10:16.622 --> 10:20.008
[Hip-hop music]

10:20.042 --> 10:21.042
What the--

10:21.060 --> 10:22.177
what just happened?

10:22.195 --> 10:24.479
That water contains
teeth dazzler,

10:24.497 --> 10:25.737
which makes your teeth stronger

10:25.748 --> 10:27.883
and starts a party
in your mouth.

10:27.917 --> 10:35.791
♪

10:40.997 --> 10:43.582
What?
Fluoride's boring, guys.

10:43.616 --> 10:44.583
Boo!

10:44.617 --> 10:46.351
Welcome to T-dazzle.

10:46.386 --> 10:47.769
It's not a chemical.

10:47.804 --> 10:50.171
It's an aquatic-based
social-media oral experience.

10:50.189 --> 10:52.474
Everyone who tweets
at T-dazzle in the next hour

10:52.492 --> 10:55.243
will be entered to win
an exciting plain blue T-shirt.

10:55.277 --> 10:57.229
I say "T,"
you say "dazzle."

10:57.263 --> 10:58.680
"T."
All: Dazzle.

10:58.714 --> 10:59.648
"T."
All: Dazzle.

10:59.682 --> 11:00.816
"T."
All: Dazzle.

11:00.850 --> 11:02.217
Thank you for
the woodworking lesson, Ron.

