This whole crib-recall thing
has got me

11:04.504 --> 11:05.604
literally rethinking everything

11:05.638 --> 11:07.139
I thought I knew
about parenting.

11:07.190 --> 11:08.523
What sleep method
will you be using--

11:08.558 --> 11:10.342
Ferber, Sears?

11:10.376 --> 11:12.527
Swanson method,

11:12.545 --> 11:14.379
where you close
your eyes and fall asleep.

11:14.414 --> 11:17.349
I really wish Ron would engage,

11:17.383 --> 11:20.936
but he exudes so much wisdom
that I can learn parenting tips

11:20.970 --> 11:22.604
simply by being
in his presence.

11:22.638 --> 11:25.624
Someone like Ron is teaching
even when they're not teaching.

11:25.658 --> 11:27.142
Does that make sense?

11:27.176 --> 11:30.178
My anxiety has kept me up
for over 50 hours.

11:30.212 --> 11:31.513
[Laughs]

11:31.547 --> 11:34.766
Our polling shows
that 72% of citizens

11:34.801 --> 11:37.002
are in favor of adding
T-dazzle to their water,

11:37.053 --> 11:39.721
effectively killing
Councilman Jamm's so-called

11:39.739 --> 11:40.906
Clean Water Bill.

11:40.940 --> 11:42.574
Eat it, Jamm.
I won.

11:42.625 --> 11:44.142
Apology accepted.

11:44.177 --> 11:45.493
You know, I've actually
come around

11:45.511 --> 11:46.795
to your way of thinking
on this.

11:46.829 --> 11:49.448
My only thought is,
why stop here?

11:49.482 --> 11:50.615
Ladies and gentlemen,

11:50.666 --> 11:53.535
Sweetums president
Jessica Wicks.

11:53.569 --> 11:55.887
[Applause]

11:55.922 --> 11:56.855
Whoo!

11:56.889 --> 12:00.425
Look, we all love T-dazzle.

12:00.460 --> 12:03.428
But we can do more to improve
our drinking supply.

12:03.463 --> 12:06.514
Sweetums is excited
to propose an alternative

12:06.532 --> 12:08.900
to boring municipal water.

12:08.951 --> 12:11.369
We call it "Drink-ems"!

12:11.420 --> 12:12.454
Whoo!

12:12.488 --> 12:14.422
Sweetums is prepared
to take over

12:14.456 --> 12:16.057
the management
of Pawnee's water.

12:16.092 --> 12:18.977
This is gonna save this town
beaucoup bucks.

12:19.028 --> 12:21.646
Take a sip
of this delicious water

12:21.697 --> 12:24.249
and imagine it coming
out of your faucets at home.

12:24.283 --> 12:26.251
This water is filled
with sugar.

12:26.285 --> 12:31.005
There's absolutely no way
we are doing this.

12:31.023 --> 12:32.941
Checkmate.

12:32.975 --> 12:34.860
Did you bring those with you
just to do that?

12:34.894 --> 12:36.361
- Maybe.
- Damn.

12:36.412 --> 12:37.645
It is a baller move.

12:37.663 --> 12:40.782
What are we gonna do now,
Leslie?

12:40.800 --> 12:42.167
Hey.

12:42.218 --> 12:44.352
Okay, are you still mad at me
about the poodle thing?

12:44.387 --> 12:45.437
It was just a dumb game.

12:45.471 --> 12:46.805
I can pick another dog.

12:46.856 --> 12:48.556
I'm not mad about the choice.

12:48.574 --> 12:50.358
I'm mad about your reasons.

12:50.392 --> 12:53.194
"Pretty," "makeup"--
is that all you know about me?

12:53.212 --> 12:55.163
We don't hang out that much.

12:55.197 --> 12:57.165
It's not like you know
a ton about me.

12:57.199 --> 12:59.634
You're beautiful,
yet cold and aloof.

12:59.668 --> 13:01.853
You pride yourself
on being a loner.

13:01.904 --> 13:04.138
You do not obey,
you choose to cooperate.

13:04.156 --> 13:05.857
And when you stop baring
your fangs to pick a mate,

13:05.908 --> 13:07.075
it's for life.

13:07.109 --> 13:08.844
And you're fiercely loyal
to your pack,

13:08.878 --> 13:12.797
which makes you
a rare black Siberian husky.

13:12.832 --> 13:15.617
That was so spot-on,
it was scary.

13:15.635 --> 13:17.969
I need to go lie down
for 45 minutes.

13:18.020 --> 13:21.189
No, an hour...

13:21.224 --> 13:22.858
a full hour.

13:22.892 --> 13:24.309
Good morning.

13:24.360 --> 13:25.861
This won't take long.

13:25.895 --> 13:28.563
Simply put, it would be madness

13:28.597 --> 13:30.448
to let Sweetums take over
our water supply

13:30.483 --> 13:31.599
and pump it full of sugar.

13:31.617 --> 13:33.151
What's next--

13:33.202 --> 13:34.936
cookie dough toothpaste?

13:34.954 --> 13:37.489
Bad example.
That would be amazing.

13:37.540 --> 13:40.909
My point is, Sweetums is an
evil, profit-hungry corporation

13:40.943 --> 13:42.160
that is ruining our health.

13:42.211 --> 13:43.995
Ever since Sweetums
opened its doors,

13:44.046 --> 13:46.114
obesity is up 100%.

13:46.132 --> 13:47.799
It's unacceptable.

13:47.833 --> 13:51.286
Down with that poison-peddling
corporate monster.

13:51.304 --> 13:53.388
Down with Sweetums!

13:53.422 --> 13:54.956
[Reporters chattering]

13:56.392 --> 13:57.475
- Hey.
- Hey.

13:57.510 --> 13:59.030
Heard about your speech.
Sounded great.

13:59.061 --> 14:01.680
I wish you could've seen it.
It felt so good.

14:01.731 --> 14:03.515
I love loose cannon-ing.

14:03.566 --> 14:05.967
You know, I love the power
of no consequences.

14:05.985 --> 14:08.636
Well, unfortunately,
there has been one consequence.

14:08.654 --> 14:12.274
I just got fired from Sweetums.

14:12.308 --> 14:15.110
Because you were embezzling...

14:15.144 --> 14:16.328
I hope.

14:18.714 --> 14:20.708
Hey, Jessica!

14:20.884 --> 14:22.251
Did you do something
to your hair?

14:22.269 --> 14:25.237
Because, sister,
you look good enough to eat.

14:25.272 --> 14:26.272
Num num num num num.

14:26.323 --> 14:28.023
What do you want, Leslie?

14:28.041 --> 14:29.425
You can't punish Ben
for something I did.

14:29.459 --> 14:30.459
It's not fair.

14:30.493 --> 14:32.511
I love him,
and I will do anything

14:32.562 --> 14:34.146
to help him get his job back.

14:34.181 --> 14:35.314
What do you want?

14:35.349 --> 14:38.084
I want you
to formally apologize

14:38.118 --> 14:39.719
for what
you said about Sweetums.

14:39.770 --> 14:42.071
I want you to say
that we're a moral,

14:42.105 --> 14:46.258
upstanding corporation that
you're proud to have in Pawnee.

14:46.293 --> 14:48.177
And when you make your apology,

14:48.211 --> 14:51.480
I want you to wear
a lime-green pantsuit

14:51.514 --> 14:53.215
because it will look horrible
on you.

14:53.250 --> 14:55.801
You are such an autumn.

14:55.852 --> 14:57.419
Did you need me for something?

14:57.437 --> 14:59.605
Yes, I want to figure out
your spirit dog,

14:59.656 --> 15:00.873
and I'm going to do that

15:00.907 --> 15:02.792
by learning everything there is
to know about you.

15:02.826 --> 15:05.094
All right. Game on.

15:05.128 --> 15:06.896
Okay, what's
your favorite color?

15:06.930 --> 15:08.898
For cars, it's gold.
For shoes, it's red--

15:08.932 --> 15:11.100
unless it's the weekend,
then reverse them.

15:11.118 --> 15:14.170
- Favorite music?
- 1970s funk and 1770s opera

15:14.204 --> 15:16.555
and Sugar Ray,
post Mark McGrath

15:16.590 --> 15:17.890
after he left
for <i>Entertainment Tonight.</i>

15:17.924 --> 15:19.525
- Favorite book?
- <i>Downton Abbey.</i>

15:19.576 --> 15:22.328
- That's not a--
- <i>Downton...Abbey.</i>

15:22.362 --> 15:23.295
Okay.

15:23.330 --> 15:25.631
Um, describe
your perfect Sunday.

15:25.665 --> 15:26.882
Church,

15:26.916 --> 15:27.933
do the <i>Harper's Magazine</i>
<i>Acrostic,</i>

15:27.968 --> 15:29.435
play my oboe in the jacuzzi

15:29.469 --> 15:31.153
while the sun sets
over puget sound.

15:31.187 --> 15:32.254
Favorite movies?

15:32.289 --> 15:33.529
In order--
<i>Natural Born Killers,</i>

15:33.540 --> 15:34.707
<i>Remains of the Day,</i>

15:34.741 --> 15:37.126
and <i>Bill & Ted's Bogus Journey.</i>

15:37.144 --> 15:39.095
Excellent.

15:39.129 --> 15:40.730
Thank you very much
for your time.

15:40.764 --> 15:43.833
I will have
your answer shortly.

15:45.085 --> 15:46.519
No idea.

15:46.553 --> 15:48.888
If a joint is
properly fashioned,

15:48.939 --> 15:51.673
all you need to do
is guide it into place.

15:51.691 --> 15:55.361
"All you need to do
is guide it into place."

15:55.412 --> 15:57.413
What I get from that is,
when parenting,

15:57.447 --> 15:59.749
sometimes a subtle hand
is more effective

15:59.783 --> 16:01.384
than a strong one.

16:01.418 --> 16:02.885
This is already
so much more helpful

16:02.919 --> 16:04.770
than the last book
on parenting I read--

16:04.821 --> 16:08.457
<i>Rad Dads</i> by Apolo Anton Ohno
and Shaun White.

16:08.492 --> 16:11.177
Nah.

16:11.211 --> 16:13.295
Ron, why did you throw
that wood away?

16:13.313 --> 16:14.763
It's unstable.
It's no good.

16:14.781 --> 16:16.231
I just don't understand

16:16.249 --> 16:18.233
"the throwing away the wood"
metaphor.

16:18.251 --> 16:19.701
What's the lesson?

16:19.719 --> 16:22.088
Oh, I know!
It's potty-training.

16:22.139 --> 16:24.706
That trash can is the toilet,
and the wood was the feces.

16:24.724 --> 16:26.692
Chris, I'm not teaching you
anything.

16:26.726 --> 16:28.027
We're just building a crib.

16:28.061 --> 16:29.278
No, I know you're not

16:29.312 --> 16:30.863
consciously teaching me
anything.

16:30.914 --> 16:32.348
I'm trying to siphon off

16:32.382 --> 16:34.350
some of your calm,
centered wisdom

16:34.384 --> 16:35.384
through metaphors.

16:35.418 --> 16:36.385
Metaphors?

16:36.403 --> 16:37.820
I hate metaphors.

16:37.854 --> 16:39.822
That's why my favorite book is
<i>Moby Dick--</i>

16:39.856 --> 16:41.907
no froufrou symbolism,

16:41.942 --> 16:44.993
just a good, simple tale
about a man who hates an animal.

16:45.011 --> 16:49.315
That's enough for today,
I think.

16:49.349 --> 16:53.752
- An organized child is a--
- No.

16:53.787 --> 16:56.422
[Sighs] Okay, I've been
working on this for three hours,

16:56.473 --> 16:58.858
and I know your spirit dog.

16:58.892 --> 17:01.861
You are a Nova Scotia toller,

17:01.895 --> 17:05.998
because you're
outgoing and adventurous.

17:06.031 --> 17:08.851
And you love Canada?

17:08.885 --> 17:11.252
- No, that's not right.
- No, it isn't.

17:11.271 --> 17:12.605
But I appreciate the effort.

17:12.638 --> 17:13.606
We're good.

17:13.656 --> 17:14.990
And don't beat yourself up.

17:15.025 --> 17:17.159
You'll probably never guess
what kind of dog I am.

17:17.194 --> 17:19.474
You're right. I'll never guess
what kind of dog you are,

17:19.496 --> 17:20.695
because you're not a dog.

17:20.714 --> 17:21.763
You're a cat.

17:21.798 --> 17:23.516
You're temperamental.

17:23.550 --> 17:26.852
You're unpredictable, complex,
and hard to read.

17:26.887 --> 17:29.655
You make people work
before you let them in.

17:29.689 --> 17:32.458
But if they put the time in
and prove that they care,

17:32.492 --> 17:34.143
then you open yourself up
to them.

17:34.177 --> 17:36.128
Right?

17:38.014 --> 17:41.383
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.

17:41.401 --> 17:44.170
Hmm.
[Purrs]

17:44.204 --> 17:46.205
"So let's all raise a glass,

17:46.239 --> 17:48.541
"full of delicious,
sugary drinking water,

17:48.575 --> 17:51.193
to Sweetums--
a Pawnee Institution."

17:51.211 --> 17:52.928
Leslie, don't do this.

17:52.963 --> 17:55.848
I have to, Ben.
We can't both be out of a job.

17:55.882 --> 17:58.050
What will we do--
sleep all day,

17:58.101 --> 17:59.718
take cooking classes together,

17:59.769 --> 18:02.188
sit on a couch
and watch movies?

18:02.222 --> 18:04.840
- God, that sounds horrible.
- There's more at stake here.

18:04.858 --> 18:07.142
I mean, you apologize,
it'll be an endorsement

18:07.176 --> 18:08.694
- for the Drink-ems plan.
- I know that, but--

18:08.728 --> 18:11.363
And everything you said
about Sweetums was right on.

18:11.398 --> 18:14.033
I mean, 90%
of the charity work I did

18:14.067 --> 18:16.402
was to compensate
for messes they caused.

18:16.453 --> 18:18.904
And I don't want to work
for them anymore.

18:18.955 --> 18:20.139
Are you sure?

18:20.173 --> 18:22.958
Yeah, just go up there,
stick to your guns.

18:22.993 --> 18:24.293
It's not gonna make
a difference.

18:24.327 --> 18:25.377
I can't beat them.

18:25.412 --> 18:27.713
All I have on my side is
facts and science,

18:27.747 --> 18:29.832
and people hate
facts and science.

18:29.866 --> 18:32.001
Wait.
I have an idea.

18:32.035 --> 18:34.253
Go get Tom.
Run! Get Tom!

18:36.098 --> 18:38.537
Yesterday I said some pretty harsh things

18:38.657 --> 18:41.826
about Sweetums
and their great new product.

18:41.946 --> 18:43.397
But when I looked
at the research,

18:43.431 --> 18:46.199
I found some pretty compelling
facts about Drink-ems

18:46.234 --> 18:48.035
that made me change my tune.

18:48.069 --> 18:50.988
Each Drink-ems is packed
with 35%

18:51.022 --> 18:54.041
of your daily monopotassium
phosphate requirement.

18:54.075 --> 18:58.328
MPP is an emulsifier as well
as a plus-7 PH buffer.

18:58.379 --> 18:59.880
Now, I know
what you're thinking--

18:59.914 --> 19:01.048
what about its molar mass?

19:01.082 --> 19:04.251
How does 136.086 grab you?

19:04.285 --> 19:06.837
[Hip-hop beat]
What the--

19:06.888 --> 19:08.805
I don't know about y'all,

19:08.840 --> 19:10.674
but Drink-ems seems
pretty boring to me,

19:10.725 --> 19:13.226
not like H-2-flow.

19:13.261 --> 19:14.511
Excuse me.

19:14.562 --> 19:16.296
I have several binders
with very important data

19:16.314 --> 19:17.597
that I need to get through.

19:17.631 --> 19:19.271
Well, miss, I think
we'd all appreciate it

19:19.300 --> 19:21.184
if you just swallowed
a teaspoon of hush.

19:21.235 --> 19:24.071
Think of H-2-flow
as an app for your teeth.

19:24.105 --> 19:27.190
The more flow you take in,
the more sparkle points you get.

19:27.241 --> 19:28.525
Get enough sparkle points,

19:28.576 --> 19:30.193
and you're on your way
to your first aqua badge!

19:30.228 --> 19:31.611
Collect enough aqua badges,

19:31.645 --> 19:36.533
and we'll welcome you
to the H-2-flow Platinum Club.

19:36.584 --> 19:39.086
I'm great at business,
and I'm great at parks stuff.

19:39.120 --> 19:40.921
I'm like Picasso meets
Michael Jordan.

19:40.955 --> 19:42.122
I can paint,

19:42.156 --> 19:45.092
but, uh, I can also be
a world-class gambler.

19:45.126 --> 19:47.044
Ron, what's this?

19:47.095 --> 19:48.879
The crib I built.

19:48.930 --> 19:50.597
I'm giving it to you and Ann.

19:50.631 --> 19:51.815
It's perfectly safe.

19:51.849 --> 19:54.317
I tested it by hitting it
with my truck.

19:54.352 --> 19:55.635
Well, Ron, I can't accept.

19:55.669 --> 19:57.337
This is for your baby.

19:57.355 --> 19:59.156
There's more than
one crib tree in a forest.

19:59.173 --> 20:00.673
That's not a lesson,
by the way,

20:00.692 --> 20:03.310
just a comment
on lumber availability.

20:03.344 --> 20:05.845
It's beautiful.
Thank you.

20:05.863 --> 20:07.864
Nobody has
all the right answers

20:07.899 --> 20:09.516
in parenting, including me.

20:09.534 --> 20:11.318
And that toxic crib you bought

20:11.352 --> 20:12.953
won't be the last mistake
you make.

20:12.987 --> 20:14.521
But a man who's this worried

20:14.539 --> 20:16.323
about making
all the right choices

20:16.357 --> 20:17.958
cares very much.

20:17.992 --> 20:19.859
That's all that matters.

20:19.877 --> 20:21.962
You'll be a great father.

20:21.996 --> 20:23.296
Thank you, Ron...

20:23.331 --> 20:25.132
for the crib and the advice.

20:25.252 --> 20:28.201
It's much better
than any metaphor.

20:28.219 --> 20:30.921
Does the white whale
actually symbolize

20:30.972 --> 20:33.340
the unknowability
and meaninglessness

20:33.374 --> 20:35.258
of human existence?

20:35.309 --> 20:37.094
[Chuckles] No.

20:37.145 --> 20:39.479
It's just a [bleep] fish.

20:39.514 --> 20:41.398
Hey, good news.

20:41.432 --> 20:42.549
Drink-ems is dead.

20:42.567 --> 20:44.784
As of tomorrow,
every Pawnee resident

20:44.802 --> 20:47.220
will have H-2-flow
in their drinking water.

20:47.255 --> 20:48.288
That's great news.

20:48.306 --> 20:50.424
H-2-flow is fluoride, right?

20:50.458 --> 20:52.476
I think so.

20:52.510 --> 20:55.562
I'll double-check with Tom,
but I'm, like, 95% sure.

20:55.596 --> 20:56.763
Wow.
Look at us.

20:56.797 --> 20:59.316
Two people, who are about
to have zero jobs.

20:59.350 --> 21:00.400
Weird, huh?

21:00.435 --> 21:01.435
And you and I--

21:01.469 --> 21:03.403
we always land
on our feet, right?

21:03.438 --> 21:04.905
- Yeah.
- Uh-oh!

21:04.939 --> 21:07.691
Guess who won
that plain blue T-shirt?

21:07.742 --> 21:08.859
No way!

21:08.910 --> 21:09.976
Look how blue it is.

21:09.994 --> 21:11.596
Wow. Things are
already looking up.

21:11.716 --> 21:13.119
Yeah!

21:13.239 --> 21:15.159
